text:
Jamaica Avenue, south side, opposite 215th Street, showing in a set of three views the Thomas Callister house.  The dwelling and outbuildings extend from 215th Street to 215th Place.  Other owners of this property were I. deB. Suydam 1860, J.B. Golder 1873, and the Golder Est. in 1891.  It is now a part of the Long Island Railroad.  This is a set of three views.

1922.
Views 1, 2 and 3.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Jamaica Avenue, south side, opposite 215th Street, showing the Thos. Callister house and outbuildings.  In the background of views 1 and 2 is seen the Long Island Railroad tracks and trains.  View No. 3 shows an additional building.  All the property seen in this view is now part of the Long Island Railroad.
